author: brane
msg: O.K., I admit this is a horrible kludge, what with having a dll-ized version
of libsvn_subr linked into mod_dav_svn. But it's better than not having
a WebDAV server on Windows, isn't it?
* INSTALL: Added a section on building and installing mod_dav_svn on Windows.
* subversion.dsw: Added the mod_dav_svn project.
* subversion/mod_dav_svn/mod_dav_svn.dsp: What the name says.

author: brane
msg: * subversion/libsvn_client/libsvn_client.dsp: Added commit_util.c.

author: cmpilato
msg: * subversion/libsvn_wc/props.c
(expand_keyword): Fixed a bunch of flub-ups in my recent entries
conversion (use the committed-date instead of text-time for Date
expansion; use the last-author instead of an uninitialized pointer
(!) for Author expansion; make the URL expansion code work the same
as the other ones; remove the now-unused 'value' variable).  Hats
off to Michael Wood <mwood@its.uct.ac.za> for suggesting one of the
fixes, and to Sander Striker <striker@apache.org> for implementing
Michael's fix.  There was just more to be done in here, though.  For
example, this function now takes an svn_wc_entry_t * as an argument
instead of a path.  We really shouldn't be re-reading an entries
file for each item in the keyword list!
(svn_wc__get_keywords): Read the entry for PATH just once for all
the keywords the function is handling at this time, and pass that
entry to the expand_keyword() helper.
